channel.title: CM Daniel CM's Wings
channel.description:
This is my favorite thing I have ever modeled. Took me about a month and a half to make, of constant modeling, 24 freaking seven. These are more less for show, but can be edited to fit in a server (re sized and lowered polygons xD). Enjoy
P.S. The reason there are so many segments is because I had tried to put into the game, so they are triangulated.
[IMG]http://i875.photobucket.com/albums/ab319/shotguna99/Angelicwings1.jpg[/img]

item.title: CM Daniel CM's Wings
item.dc:creator: @the_wanderer The Wanderer
item.description:
@the_wanderer wrote:

Problems I have with the model ;):

[ul][li]You took the wireframe picture with points on.[/li]
[li]Should never triangulate a model before taking a picture, now we can’t see the wireframe. :([/li]
[li]It’s yellow[/li]
[li]They don’t really look like wings, more like one wing that was crudely pasted on the other side. I feel like wings should be structured differently, as far as anatomy goes.[/li]
[li]The feathers near the end seem out of place. Like they were just pasted there.[/li][/ul]

item.title: CM Daniel CM's Wings
item.dc:creator: @TheCyberMan TheCyberMan
item.description:
@TheCyberMan wrote:

[quote=“CM Daniel CM, post:16, topic:415593”]Thanks cyber, I myself honestly do not care if it has alot of vertcies, or segments, or whatever. I think I did a damn good job. You are all entitled to your own opionions, But if you have nothing good to say, dont say anything at all. Thank-you cyber for all your good comments about my work. I had put alot of time and effort into this model. I would encourage everyone to try and be nicer to people. Nobodies perfect. I have my own way of making models, you all have your own. So try to motivate people to keep doing their work the way they feel best. Even if you do not like it, try to motivate the creator to make another, eventually the person will get better.

Even without Triangulating it, its still a major polygon overkill. Wanna Share how many faces are on that?

8124…[/quote]
There are a lot of really good modelers on this forum. They’re just trying to share their advice. Realistically, in a game, this would be much harder to render than if this were made with however they recommend
